{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"metadata":{"title":"PIDFile","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"type":"text","text":". The file contains the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other commands ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","